[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] Each repository section defines a section name and at least one location where the packages can be found.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] The section name is defined by the string within square brackets (the two above are *core* and *custom*).
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] Repository names must be unique and the name *local* is reserved for the database of installed packages.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] Locations are defined with the *Server* directive and follow a URL naming structure.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] If you want to use a local directory, you can specify the full path with a “file://” prefix, as shown above.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] A common way to define DB locations utilizes the *Include* directive.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] For each repository defined in the configuration file, a single *Include* directive can contain a file that lists the servers for that repository.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] The order of repositories in the configuration files matters; repositories listed first will take precedence over those listed later in the file when packages in two repositories have identical names, regardless of version number.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] A full URL to a location where the packages, and signatures (if available) for this repository can be found.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] Cache servers will be tried before any non-cache servers, will not be removed from the server pool for 404 download errors, and will not be used for database files.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] A full URL to a location where the database, packages, and signatures (if available) for this repository can be found.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] During parsing, pacman will define the $repo variable to the name of the current section.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] This is often utilized in files specified using the *Include* directive so all repositories can use the same mirrorfile. pacman also defines the $arch variable to the first (or only) value of the Architecture option, so the same mirrorfile can even be used for different architectures.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] Set the signature verification level for this repository.
[src:pacman-arch/pacman-conf] Set the usage level for this repository.
